data.chText: 见多识广的；老练的；见过世面的
data.enText: having a lot of experience of the world and knowing about fashion, culture and other things that people think are socially important

data.chText: 城市生活中五花八门的享乐
data.enText: the sophisticated pleasures of city life

data.chText: 马克是一个聪明老成的年轻人。
data.enText: Mark is a smart and sophisticated young man.

data.chText: 复杂巧妙的；先进的；精密的
data.enText: clever and complicated in the way that it works or is presented

data.chText: 十分先进的计算机系统
医疗技术日益复杂精妙。
data.enText: Medical techniques are becoming more sophisticated all the time.
able to understand difficult or complicated ideas

tr: having or appealing to those having worldly knowledge and refinement and savoir-faire

value.def: A sophisticated machine, device, or method is more advanced or complex than others.

example.ex: Honeybees use one of the most sophisticated communication systems of any insect.
example.tran: 蜜蜂之间所用的交流方式是昆虫中最为复杂的方式之一。

example.ex: ...a large and sophisticated new British telescope.
example.tran: 一架崭新的大型英式精密望远镜

value.tran: (机器、装置等)高级的，精密的;(方法)复杂的

value.def: Someone who is sophisticated is comfortable in social situations and knows about culture, fashion, and other matters that are considered socially important.

example.ex: Claude was a charming, sophisticated companion...
example.tran: 克劳德是一个很有魅力、见多识广的伙伴。

example.ex: Recently her tastes have become more sophisticated.
example.tran: 最近她的品位越发优雅时髦起来。

value.tran: 善于社交的;高雅时髦的;见过世面的

value.def: A sophisticated person is intelligent and knows a lot, so that they are able to understand complicated situations.

example.ex: These people are very sophisticated observers of the foreign policy scene.
example.tran: 这些人是观察外交政策领域动向的行家里手。

value.tran: 精明老练的;老于世故的
